Our mission is still to provide the best possible learning opportunities for our students! We are still learning and growing and finding our way through this crisis.

Canvas is a new tool that will help us house all of your virtual learning in one, easy to access, place. Paper packets will still be set home weekly, so choose what works best for you and your family. We will support you no matter where you are in this process. We are here for you LPA!

post_text: We are excited to see what PBS has to offer students throughout the state of Ohio! Take some time to check it out and let us know what you think.
shared_text:
Ohio Department of Education
March 27 at 5:16 PM ·

📺📝📚 Working together to support Ohio's students!

Beginning Monday, March 30, Ohio’s eight PBS stations will air grade-level appropriate, standards-based programs for students as part of their new #LearnAtHome initiative. Check your local listings for the full schedule.

The educational teams at each station will provide additional resources related to the new programming schedule.

Visit http://pbslearningmedia.org to access free online resources for educators and students.

The Ohio Broadcast Educational Media Commission shares more details here: https://broadcast.ohio.gov/Portals/0/Images/ProjectSpotlight/OhioPublicBroadcastersUnite_NewsRelease_3_26_2020.pdf

#InThisTogetherOhio #OhioEd

post_text: Instructions for how to access Lorain County Job and Family Services during this closure period.
shared_text:
Lorain County Job and Family Services
March 19 at 7:16 AM ·

The LCDJFS LOBBY is closed until further notice.

There is a dropbox outside the main lobby for clients to drop off verifications.

You can apply for cash, food and medical assistance by calling 1-844-640-6446.

You can also complete applications online at http://www.benefits.ohio.gov.
Verifications can also be uploaded to your Ohio Benefits account, or emailed to: michael.schmittgen@jfs.ohio.gov.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Hasta nuevo aviso nuestros recepciones estan cerradas

Hay un buzón afuera de la recepcion principal para que los clientes entreguen las verificaciones.

Puede solicitar asistencia médica, alimentaria y en efectivo llamando al 1-844-640-6446.

También puede completar las solicitudes en línea en http://www.benefits.ohio.gov.

Las verificaciones también se pueden cargar a su cuenta de Beneficios de Ohio, o enviarse por correo electrónico a: michael.schmittgen@jfs.ohio.gov

post_text: The Lady Lions remain undefeated after beating Lake Ridge Academy. Final score 29-19. Balycia had 17 points bringing her over the 100 point mark for the season. Makya was coach Jakab's top defensive player. Great Game Ladies!! The boys and girls play a double header tomorrow starting at 4:30 in the LPA gym. Come root for your Lions!!
